1817	WRIT	2330	Creative Writing: Short Story	A workshop course in reading and writing varied forms of short narrative and non-narrative prose fiction; students must have a good command of written English and grammar. This course will focus on reading and analyzing exemplary short fiction and writing and revising original work. Students learn to develop plot, character, setting, point of view, style, and theme, and use description effectively to invent and shape narrative strategies. Peer reading and writing groups offer opportunities for shared response and critique.	0	0	0	1	1	0	{"Well-being: Body and Mind"}
